4579	   elements (lz77size >= 1 covers index 0). The splitpoints are the sorted,
4580	   ascending block boundaries supplied by the caller; sortedness makes end >=
4581	   start so the unsigned `end - start` cannot wrap, which is what lets the
4582	   postcondition observe *lend > *lstart. npoints <= 4 matches the --unwind 5
